medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Gradual onset of substernal chest pain, initially with cutting/tearing sensation and concern for pain radiating to the back, but later evaluated as more mild. Associated symptoms included nausea, vomiting, and epigastric pain. Upon further evaluation, chest pain and back pain resolved, but abdominal pain in RUQ and RLQ developed.
